title: For Sale:  SPAS 12 With Folding Stock and Arm Hook
postcontent:
I have an iconic SPAS 12, straight out of Jurassic Park.

Very important: It has the safety upgrade from the recall, this has the push button cross bolt safety instead of the dangerous rotating safety.  This is hard to find and no more safety retrofits have been available for 20 years.  This is a very desirable upgrade.

The plastic swivel loop on the top of the pistol grip is missing as is the detent and spring that holds the stock folded.  The all parts are present otherwise, including the hook so the shotgun can be fired one handed.  This is usually missing.

Fun to shoot, iconic and a collectors item.  Don't miss this one.  Prefer a face to face deal or in state, but can ship for the right terms.

title: For Sale:  Erma Werke 26.5mm Flare Pistol Outfit
postcontent:
Folks this is a very uncommon post war, 4 KAL (26.5mm) flare pistol made by Erma Werke of Germany. I've collected old military arms & flare guns for 37 years and have only seem similar pistols two or three times. In fact many more of the wartime models were imported and are much more commonly seen, but you can look and look and may never find one exactly like this. There must not have been many brought over.  

This pistol was made in 1957 and was issued to East German troops. It's really in great condition and has 90% or more of it's original metal finish. The grips are excellent as well and the bore is bright & shiny with no signs of rust, pitting or corrosion whatsoever. It's all metal construction and was made at a time when high quality was the norm. It's construction is far superior to the more modern versions from the 70's & 80's that relied heavily on plastics.  

Everything is perfect mechanically and this pistol can and will fire. It's also safe to shoot with the flare and smoke cartridges it was designed to fire.  

Pistol comes with a correct & original East German black leather holster with shoulder strap. Correct leather lanyard. Plus 26.5mm cleaning rod and cleaning brush.Additionally there is an adapter that allows the more common and less expensive 12 gauge flares to be fired.  

Finally there are (8) live 26.5mm rounds included: (2) orange smoke, (2) white parachute illumination, (2) red star & (2) green star. There are also (6) 12 gauge Red Meteor shells made by Orion.   

This is a true collectors item that you can have some fun with since shooting it won't devalue it as long as you clean it up afterwards.  

Asking price for the whole setup is $350 with pickup in Brandon. You must be at least 18 to purchase.

WORKS WITH 22 LR, 17 HMR, 22MAG, 5.7X28 The 22Sparrow is the first silencer in the world to offer the patent pending Multi Part Containment (MPC) technology, which allows the 22Sparrow to be easily disassembled for cleaning and maintenance after heavy use. Because the .22 LR round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time, it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue, .22 silencers must be disassembled for cleaning and regular maintenance. MPC technology has made it possible for shooters to disassemble the 22Sparrow easily after heavy use without the need of tools. Until Silencerco introduced the 22Sparrow, the only .22 silencers that could be disassembled for cleaning required a cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds. However, often the components of those silencers would be fused together and unable to come apart. Competitor products on the market have baffles in their .22 silencers that must be removed by twisting the outer tube around the baffles and/or sliding the outer tube off of the baffles. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the outer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the outer tube, there is simply too much buildup of fouling and lead to remove the outer tube in that manner. Silencerco solved this maintenance issue with MPC technology and made it possible for shooters to disassemble the 22Sparrow easily after heavy use without the need of tools. MPC technology revolutionized take-apart silencers by containing the lead and carbon debris to prevent the debris from reaching the outer tube. This innovative design is achieved by applying two tube halves before sliding the outer tube on the rest of the assembly. When disassembling, the outer tube can be easily removed, and the tube halves are free to pull away from the baffles without having to rotate or slide. Just pull off the tubes, clean the components, and reassemble.Silencers are legal but they are regulated on a per-state basis. It is legal to purchase and possess silencers in 38 states. However, for dealers, manufacturers, peace officers, or a law enforcement or government agency,Individual, there are additional states where you can own a silencer. One on the comb and one on the stock itself.  It is very hard to see either of them and neither appear to penetrate past the finish.

The gun also comes with an Orvis Battenkill green canvas and leather take-down case.  The case features a very plush fleece lining and comes with both a handle and a substantial adjustable carrying strap.  I did have it personalized with my initials.  The case alone sells for $169 new.
